## What's covered

**Email** — type/null-byte/length (RFC 5321: 254 total, 64 local), exactly-one `@`, consecutive-dot, leading/trailing dot, header-injection (CR/LF), whitespace, IDN→punycode encoding with invalid-IDN rejection, IP-literal & `localhost` rejection, TLD presence, disposable-domain blocking, `email-validator` as authoritative pass, NFKC normalization, and a separate **canonical key** (Gmail dot/plus folding) used only for uniqueness — not for the stored address.

**Username** — length 3–30, charset allowlist, no edge/consecutive separators, reserved-word blocking, offensive-substring blocking, **homoglyph defense** (de-confuse Cyrillic/lookalikes → ASCII before reserved/offensive comparison; e.g. Cyrillic `аdmin` is caught), ASCII-only enforcement, case-insensitive uniqueness via `username_lower`.

